<br>
Seriously, I would say it depends on what you are looking for.  If all you want is exp, then you can't beat a good group, especially at 60.  As an enc, I feel that I turn a good group into a great one, and a great group into a memorable one.  We are not meant to put out damage, can't take damage for very long, and have to rely on regen or others when we do.<br>
<br>
If you want to work on faction, then the risk of a broken charm on a green mob isn't so bad.<br>
If you normally play for short periods of time and can't waste time looking for a group, then I'd suggest finding some nice caster mobs without too many friends and use the old Nuke-n-Mez method, with some ToT anytime you can to limit downtime.<br>
<br>
Ishana Windgiver<br>
60 Enchanter of Tunare<br>
Erolissi Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ualanovsinpreyus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alanov Sin Preyus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(2/27/02 6:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: charm soloing</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't recommend using charm as a means of XPing. It can backfire too easily. If solo, definitely do not use it ... because if it backfires it is you against at least two mobs. The only times I use charm is when grouping/raiding against unmezzable mobs and occasionally when in a full group as an extra tank ... but only then if the group knows they need to get my back if the charm breaks and my ex-pet is beating on me. If you do try charm though ... always have at least one stun up, root and mez ... as all can be used against your pissed off ex-pet.<br>
<br>
