nish him. <p>DISCLAIMER:<BR>This is my opinion.  As such, it should not be taken as fact even though I believe it to be so.  Everyone is entitiled to thier own opinions and as much of a voice to them as is given me.  Please do not judge my words too harshly.  They are only my words and as such, are only as powerful as you make them.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/udunder1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunder1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(7/29/02 3:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> charm solo is easy</span><hr size=1>  Hey, I was charm soloing at 36 in Rathe Mountains. SoW is critical. But alas, GIANTS can be charmed to great effect. Is a dangerous career path, but very enjoyable to watch the faces (text) of the all the others hunting HG's. So, I know soloing is very much possible at 60. Just don't expect to wipe out dragons by yourself, even with DIRE CHARM.<br>
<br>
 Donder, 40, Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uslymie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>slymie</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#330000>(7/29/02 6:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: charm solo is easy</span><hr size=1> If yer lvl 60 and don't have the time to get a group yer best bet for  soloing is velks. But NOT with charm. Use yer pet. /gasp!! /rude!!! MY PET!!?? you say? Yup. Get some dink weapons so it duel weilds. SUmmon him up, haste him, buff yerself fully, illusion fire elemental, and DS yerself, then cast bedlam and boon of garou.<br>
<br>
Find a spider, tash, then slow it. Pet will engage. The rest is simply standing there meleeing it and replaceing yer bedlam when it runs out. I usually use about 10-15% mana on reg spiders, and 20-40% on devourers. Once ya get the spider slowed they are chump. Yer lvl 55 pet will max hit for wuad 54's and kicks in the 30's. So it's dishing out some real damage. The thing is that your AC is prob better than yer pets. Add to that the extra 16 point DS from your illusion and thats the reason YOU stay in melee instead of letting your pet tank.<br>
<br>
Sounds totally insane, but it works and is pretty damn easy. Adds can be mezzed as necessary, just watch out for the backstabbing spiders. They can ruin yer whole day. <p><font size="2" face="Verdana,Arial">
